review:
FromSoftware is not for me, but I keep buying because of the hype and keep getting disappointed by what makes this such an award-winning experience:
It's damn hard (no, really);
Even the terrain hates you;
Nothing is linear and Google is your friend;
Story? I'll tell you bits and pieces and you figure the rest out yourself someday, if ever.
Graphics? AAA (How many A's can you put here?)
Music? Lots of A's
Creature design? I'm running out of A's
Enemy variety? You have more enemies than you did in highschool.

try fingers,

but hole

to be serious though, I avoided this game for the last year because it felt like there was *too much* hype around it, like it would be another Cyberpunk. That was definitely not the case, the game absolutely lives up to the hype and feels immensely satisfying to play

amazing game until endgame, where it falls off hard - bosses are hit or miss, map design is pretty much linear after leyndell which means worse exploration (which was the game's best feature up until this point);
also game has waaaaay too much copypasting of bosses, which maybe can be excused for many of the enemies, but bosses like astel and godrick just shouldn't be reused;
elden beast is a disappointing final boss both in gameplay (due to lack of torrent) and story (radagon is hyped up the whole game and elden beast shows up unexpectedly as phase two)
